TY  - JOUR
T1  - Prospect Theory Explains Newsvendor Behavior: The Role of Reference Points
AU  - Long, Xiaoyang
AU  - Nasiry, Javad
Y1  - 2014/12/11
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2015/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.2014.2050
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.2014.2050
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 3009
EP  - 3012
VL  - 61
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Current understanding in operations management is that prospect theory, as a theory of decision making under uncertainty, cannot systematically explain the ordering behavior observed in experiments on the newsvendor problem. We suggest this is because the newsvendor?s reference point is assumed to be the status quo, i.e., zero payoff. We propose an alternative based on newsvendor?s salient payoffs and show that prospect theory can, in fact, account for experimental results. This paper was accepted by Serguei Netessine, operations management.
